1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,320
Take this.

2
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:44,640
It's difficult now.
If this neighborhood doesn't welcome you,

3
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:45,760
how are you supposed
to open a school here?

4
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:48,080
<i>Everything started with me,</i>
<i>so it has to end with me.</i>

5
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:49,720
I need to face the truth.

6
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:53,320
Don't tell me you're going to admit
that you were the one driving that car.

7
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:55,320
She pressured me
to take responsibility for you.

8
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:57,840
I'm very disappointed in you, Pakbung.

9
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:00,440
<i>Do you seriously not see</i>

10
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:03,000
Darin's trying to force her way
back into your life?

11
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:04,600
We caused this together,

12
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,160
so we'll get through it together.

13
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:08,080
You won't leave me, right?

14
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:11,520
<i>Just tell me straight.</i>

15
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:13,280
Be a man.

16
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:14,560
Who are you choosing?

17
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:17,280
Me or your ex?

18
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,800
Choose.

19
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:25,040
<i>Pakbung is my girlfriend.</i>

20
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,560
Why are you messing with her?

21
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:29,760
If you can't take care of Pakbung,
then I will.

22
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,720
This time, Rachen knocked me out cold.

23
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:44,920
I took a full hook punch.

24
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:49,040
Your brother loves being dramatic.

25
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:53,800
Honestly, I can just pay
the water bill, and that's it.

26
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:56,320
But I should pay more attention to you.

27
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:58,960
I should help you solve your problems.

28
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:01,760
If your beautiful girlfriend

29
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,800
can't handle something this small,

30
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:06,440
wouldn't that be a bigger problem?

31
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:18,120
According to National Geographic research,

32
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,640
drinking bubble tea

33
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:24,360
helps you feel refreshed,
energized, and less stressed.

34
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:27,000
Wait. National Geographic?

35
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:28,720
Yes.

36
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:32,240
The wildlife documentary channel.
They guarantee it's good.

37
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:34,840
Try it.

38
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:46,760
Whoa, no wonder people like it.

39
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:49,760
So, shall we be bubble tea for each other?

40
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:53,840
Be each other's refreshment,
recharge each other.

41
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:55,960
We already are.

42
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,560
But

43
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:03,040
bubble tea is good for the heart,

44
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:04,920
not good for the body.

45
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,800
Today, I didn't work again.

46
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,880
And you…

47
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:14,840
left your business to come see me.

48
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:17,920
Do you think that's something good?

49
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,040
Wait.

50
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:24,240
Why are you talking like
what we have right now isn't okay?

51
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:26,640
What's on your mind?

52
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:29,160
Don't tell me you want to break up.

53
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:32,440
No, not break up.

54
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:35,240
I do like bubble tea,

55
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:38,040
and I'm not switching to herbal drinks.

56
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:40,360
But I can't drink it all the time.

57
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:42,080
Same with you.

58
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:44,520
Otherwise,

59
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:48,000
diabetes, high blood pressure,
high cholesterol will come knocking.

60
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:52,160
Even if you love something,
you need the right distance.

61
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:54,120
Don't you think?

62
00:05:59,000 --> 00:05:59,840
SAHARAT

63
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,520
I'd like to apply for a job.

64
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,080
Sorry. Every position is filled.
Sorry about that.

65
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:08,480
AUTO REPAIR

66
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:11,280
We only hire experienced workers.

67
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:12,320
Alright?

68
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:13,680
- Good luck.
- Okay.

69
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:20,760
Why is it so hard to find a job?

70
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:25,000
Yut.

71
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,120
Are you looking for a job?

72
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,760
Why are you looking for a job?

73
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:36,120
Do what you're good at.

74
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:39,200
This is my den.

75
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:42,120
Daily cash flow
in the hundreds of thousands.

76
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:44,720
No one interferes.
I pay everyone properly.

77
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:58,720
No.

78
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:01,720
I don't want my kids
to be disappointed in me again.

79
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,240
Yut.

80
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:08,720
Are you sure your kids
aren't already disappointed in you?

81
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:11,280
I don't believe it.

82
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:21,200
Here. For you.

83
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:28,280
Money? Where did you get it?

84
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:33,200
Dad was worried you'd think he's a burden,
so he went looking for work since morning.

85
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:37,720
At first, I almost didn't get anything.

86
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:41,160
Then I ran into a friend
who runs a BBQ buffet.

87
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:43,120
He asked me to sing.

88
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:46,200
I played guitar and sang.
With tips included,

89
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:47,840
I got quite a bit.

90
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:00,680
I don't smell any grilled food.

91
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,920
Are you a police dog?

92
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,640
Why are you sniffing for evidence?

93
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:12,440
Dad earned money.
Just take it and thank him.

94
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:19,240
Well… Thank you.

95
00:08:19,320 --> 00:08:22,400
Hey, what did you teach me as a kid?

96
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:25,560
When you say thank you, what do you do?
Hands?

97
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,600
Thank you,

98
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,799
but you really did sing, right?

99
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:39,159
Of course.

100
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:40,600
Hey.

101
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:44,200
This good-looking, talented singer

102
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:47,400
is the father of the two of you,
Pakbung and Kanah.

103
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:50,240
Pakbung.

104
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:53,760
Hey. I'll earn even more.

105
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:56,480
Water bill, electricity, food, everything,

106
00:08:56,560 --> 00:08:58,520
I'll take care of it.

107
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,440
Now that I'm here,

108
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:04,120
you two won't have to struggle anymore.

109
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:07,800
It's okay, Dad.

110
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:10,440
Just having you here makes me happy.

111
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:12,560
Hug?

112
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,400
- Thank you.
- It's alright.

113
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:17,760
Bung, come here.

114
00:09:18,880 --> 00:09:22,120
Bung, come here.

115
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,120
Bung.

116
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,360
Hey!

117
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:33,680
Come on!

118
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,400
Hey.

119
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,880
Should we squeeze tighter, Pakbung?

120
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:48,480
Was this part of your plan too?

121
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:53,600
I bailed you out to deal with Trai,

122
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:55,560
not to stalk this leech.

123
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:57,760
Keep watching.

124
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:03,240
HIGH, LOW

125
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,800
He's back at the gambling den again?

126
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:07,200
Why show this to Mom?

127
00:10:07,280 --> 00:10:10,280
Ms. Mika, do you still want
revenge on Pakbung?

128
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:15,720
Pakbung has no idea

129
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:18,960
her father's back at the den,
gambling almost every day.

130
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:23,360
His addiction to gambling can be useful.

131
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:25,640
Right.

132
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:28,800
Since we're already
going to deal with Trai,

133
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:32,400
why not take all of them down at once?

134
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:43,560
<i>Everyone,</i>

135
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:46,480
<i>the former actress</i>
<i>whose name starts with D</i>

136
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:51,120
<i>has just admitted that</i>
<i>she caused a fatal car accident years ago.</i>

137
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,240
THE CHAOS OF STEPMOM D. AND STEPSON T.

138
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:53,520
<i>That's brutal!</i>

139
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,760
<i>And now a leaked clip has surfaced</i>

140
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:59,880
<i>saying she had a personal grudge</i>
<i>against her late husband.</i>

141
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:04,120
<i>He never gave me anything,</i>
<i>not even a single baht.</i>

142
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:06,840
<i>Even Lee and Prarop got something,</i>
<i>but I got nothing.</i>

143
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:11,160
<i>You bastard. You dirty old man.</i>

144
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:17,120
That's Ms. Darin's voice.

145
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:19,600
But it's clearly edited.

146
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:24,440
<i>But the real issue</i>
<i>is whether this former actress</i>

147
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:27,800
<i>had a thing with Mr. T,</i>

148
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:31,560
<i>the son of her husband.</i>

149
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:34,280
<i>Are they still involved?</i>

150
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,080
<i>The online world is already suspicious.</i>

151
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:39,000
<i>What exactly is going on</i>
<i>between this stepmother and stepson?</i>

152
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:40,760
<i>Or could they</i>

153
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:43,640
<i>have been involved in the death of Mr. TT?</i>

154
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:46,680
<i>This story is definitely one to follow.</i>

155
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:49,400
They're clearly trying to stir it up,
saying Mr. Trai and Ms. Darin

156
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:51,520
teamed up to kill Mr. Tritot.

157
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:55,920
These keyboard warriors are brutal.

158
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:59,960
Calling them a trash family,
saying the father and son took turns.

159
00:12:02,880 --> 00:12:04,840
Only one page is reporting this now.

160
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:07,120
But it has nearly a million followers.

161
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:10,320
Rut is probably trying to use
pressure on social media to mess with you.

162
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:13,480
Mrs. Mookmanee's probably using this
to manipulate the stock price too.

163
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,520
Lee,

164
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:21,480
call a board meeting for Be Rich.

165
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:25,040
- Yes, sir.
- Prarop, can you check

166
00:12:25,120 --> 00:12:27,240
if this page has ever reported
fake news before?

167
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:31,120
Or if it has ever been paid
to discredit someone?

168
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,240
Check those for me.

169
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:33,160
Yes, sir.

170
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:39,200
Hello, Pakbung.

171
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:41,560
You saw the news
about me and Da, right? It's nothing.

172
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:43,640
I'm not worried about that.

173
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,160
Are you okay?

174
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,000
I'm fine.

175
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,960
I've grown a thick skin now.

176
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:53,760
This can't hurt me. Don't worry.

177
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:54,880
Pakbung!

178
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:57,040
- Pakbung!
- Stop.

179
00:12:57,120 --> 00:13:00,800
If you're reporting about Mr. Trai,
no need. I'm faster.

180
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:03,040
Your dad got arrested!

181
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:04,560
- Huh?!
- Huh?!

182
00:13:07,040 --> 00:13:08,400
Pakbung? Pakbung?

183
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:13,960
Trai. Trai.

184
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:17,680
Trai, help me!

185
00:13:18,280 --> 00:13:19,280
Please help me.

186
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,880
If it's about the news, he's handling it.

187
00:13:22,520 --> 00:13:23,720
Trai.

188
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:26,480
My neighbor called.

189
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:30,240
My mom saw the news and fainted.
She hit her head.

190
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:33,080
She's at the hospital now.

191
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:34,840
She's still unconscious.

192
00:13:44,560 --> 00:13:45,600
Come on down.

193
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:56,600
Pakbung?

194
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:01,480
Pakbung, listen to me first.

195
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:07,000
This is the BBQ singing job?
And I believed you?

196
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:09,320
Pakbung, I'm sorry.

197
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:13,560
I tried finding work, but no one hired me.

198
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:17,160
I don't want to live off you
for the rest of my life.

199
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:21,440
I wanted to earn money.
I wanted you two to live comfortably.

200
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:24,800
Enough. Stop talking.

201
00:14:24,880 --> 00:14:26,680
If you want to talk, go inside.

202
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:28,920
Go, please.

203
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:32,360
Pakbung, you're bailing me out, right?

204
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:37,960
This is the money you gave me.

205
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:42,240
The gambling money.

206
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:45,520
Take it back.

207
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:50,760
It's my fault
for expecting something different.

208
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:54,160
That's why I'm disappointed.

209
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:56,880
It's my fault.

210
00:14:57,480 --> 00:15:00,520
But you cannot disappoint Kanah.

211
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:05,480
Kanah must never know about this.

212
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:07,000
Please go.

213
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:09,800
- Go.
- Pakbung.

214
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:11,800
Pakbung, I'm sorry.

215
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:12,840
Pakbung.

216
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:34,560
You alright?

217
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:44,960
I'm okay.

218
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:49,000
I just need some quiet time.

219
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:52,440
Thank you, Niuniu.

220
00:16:11,880 --> 00:16:12,960
Mr. Trai.

221
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:20,680
Look at your face.
You're not even trying to hide it.

222
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:23,840
I don't have the energy to pretend.

223
00:16:23,920 --> 00:16:26,040
Then have some sugar.

224
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:27,720
It might make you feel better.

225
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:34,760
I heard about your dad.

226
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:37,360
I let him back into my life,

227
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:40,360
so I have to accept the hurt.

228
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:45,520
It's not wrong to trust someone,
especially someone you love.

229
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:50,160
Actually, I thought
I wouldn't drink this that often.

230
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:52,840
I saw you order it a lot.
I thought you liked it.

231
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:55,120
I can throw it away.

232
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:05,640
It's sweet.

233
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:10,440
I was the one who told Mr. Trai

234
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,520
that we

235
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:16,599
didn't have to be together all the time.

236
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:19,640
That when he has things to handle,

237
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:22,880
we should give each other space.

238
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:25,800
But right now…

239
00:17:27,119 --> 00:17:28,880
I want to see him more than ever.

240
00:17:30,040 --> 00:17:31,720
I want him here with me.

241
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:37,120
I'm so contradictory, right?

242
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:42,320
No, Pakbung. You're just hurt.
That's why you're confused.

243
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:46,520
Rest a little. It'll get better.

244
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:48,480
Trust me.

245
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:52,000
I think it's too hard.

246
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:54,760
When I love someone so much,

247
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:58,040
like I love my dad, like I love Mr. Trai…

248
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:01,800
I can't control anything.

249
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:09,760
Maybe…

250
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:13,800
I'm not meant to be in love.

251
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:02,320
Are you sure you won't bail your dad out?

252
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:05,840
I can help you.

253
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:09,920
I don't want to see his face right now.

254
00:19:10,680 --> 00:19:12,080
Hey, she's here.

255
00:19:12,160 --> 00:19:14,080
- How are you?
- Yeah.

256
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:17,600
Chill. I'm used to it.

257
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:20,560
Where's Mr. Trai?
Didn't he come down with you?

258
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:22,520
Mr. Trai came here?

259
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:27,080
Oh? I saw him rushing upstairs to
find you, so I thought you'd already met.

260
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:41,440
I shouldn't have gone back to gamble…

261
00:19:50,280 --> 00:19:52,680
Mr. Yongyut. Someone's here
to bail you out.

262
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:54,440
- Me?
- Yes.

263
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:58,600
Pakbung… You forgave me.

264
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:10,920
Um… I have to thank you, Mr. Trai,

265
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:12,320
for bailing me out.

266
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:14,760
If it weren't for you, I'd be done for.

267
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:18,440
Pakbung asked you
to come bail me out, right?

268
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:19,560
No.

269
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:26,720
Mr. Yongyut,

270
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:30,480
you know Pakbung loves you
and cares about you a lot, right?

271
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:33,280
You're the biggest wound in her life.

272
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:35,600
It really left a deep scar on her
when you left.

273
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:39,160
She was hurt so badly that she was
too afraid to love anyone again.

274
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:41,320
And it took so much

275
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:43,280
for Pakbung to overcome that fear

276
00:20:43,360 --> 00:20:45,640
and give you another chance.

277
00:20:46,680 --> 00:20:48,600
So why did you destroy that so easily?

278
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:53,120
Mr. Yongyut, I'm begging you.

279
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:56,200
If you truly love your children,

280
00:20:57,800 --> 00:21:01,160
don't make Pakbung and Kanah
disappointed in you again.

281
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:11,000
MR. TRAI

282
00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:22,880
Oh? Bung?

283
00:21:22,960 --> 00:21:26,520
You're home? I thought you went to work.

284
00:21:28,640 --> 00:21:29,800
I just got back.

285
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:33,560
Where's Dad?

286
00:21:39,720 --> 00:21:40,680
Probably at work.

287
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:44,800
Oh, right. I forgot Dad's a hard worker.

288
00:21:50,720 --> 00:21:53,320
Hey, do you want to go eat BBQ
at that place today?

289
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:56,520
The one where Dad sings.
Let's surprise him.

290
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:58,080
What do you say?

291
00:21:59,760 --> 00:22:02,360
You know where it is?

292
00:22:03,240 --> 00:22:05,600
Uh, right. But it's fine.

293
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:06,880
I'll just call him and ask.

294
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:16,120
Kanah.

295
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:22,120
What if… Dad… doesn't come back…

296
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:26,240
Dad!

297
00:22:27,280 --> 00:22:29,640
I was just about to call you.

298
00:22:29,720 --> 00:22:31,560
You're not going to sing today?

299
00:22:38,280 --> 00:22:42,040
Uh, I forgot my wallet.

300
00:22:42,120 --> 00:22:43,040
I don't know where I left it.

301
00:22:43,680 --> 00:22:45,560
It's okay, Dad. I'll help you find it.

302
00:22:46,960 --> 00:22:48,080
Where is it?

303
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:49,840
Not under the cushion…

304
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:52,000
Bung, did you sit on it?

305
00:22:55,360 --> 00:22:56,560
It's not here.

306
00:22:57,160 --> 00:22:59,800
Maybe it's in the bedroom.
I'll check, Dad.

307
00:23:09,880 --> 00:23:10,880
Kanah.

308
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:15,080
I'm going out to buy something.

309
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:20,960
Oh? Bung.

310
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:22,520
Bung. Oh?

311
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:24,280
What?

312
00:23:26,080 --> 00:23:28,720
I'll keep looking, Dad.
I have no idea where it is.

313
00:23:40,040 --> 00:23:41,000
Damn it!

314
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:43,680
What is it with my life?

315
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:49,000
Damn it!

316
00:23:50,560 --> 00:23:51,600
Does it hurt?

317
00:23:55,560 --> 00:23:57,080
You're still here?

318
00:24:09,840 --> 00:24:10,840
I was waiting for you.

319
00:24:11,520 --> 00:24:12,640
Don't tell me

320
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:15,360
you're the one who bailed my dad out.

321
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:16,640
Yeah. It was me.

322
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:20,280
I didn't ask you to.
Why did you bail him out?

323
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:23,920
I don't want to see his face,
and I don't want to see yours either.

324
00:24:26,800 --> 00:24:27,960
You're mad, aren't you?

325
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:30,360
Yeah. I'm furious.

326
00:24:30,440 --> 00:24:32,200
Then let it out.

327
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:36,320
He lied to me.

328
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:40,320
He said he was going to work,
going to sing.

329
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:41,880
And he ended up at the gambling den.

330
00:24:42,600 --> 00:24:45,960
Same old habit. Every time, it's the same.

331
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:48,120
Why did he have to lie?

332
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:52,560
Why trick me into believing him
if he's not going to change for real?

333
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:54,840
Why come back at all?

334
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:56,960
Why come back?!

335
00:24:57,480 --> 00:24:58,960
Damn it!

336
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:14,680
Damn it…

337
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:19,040
Damn it…

338
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:35,800
I'm sorry.

339
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:38,560
I shouldn't have let it out on you.

340
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:41,240
It's good.

341
00:25:41,960 --> 00:25:43,880
Letting it out helps.

342
00:25:44,720 --> 00:25:46,680
Why did you have to help him get out?

343
00:25:49,520 --> 00:25:50,880
If he stayed in there,

344
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:53,600
you wouldn't be happy anyway.

345
00:25:58,160 --> 00:25:59,360
True.

346
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:03,160
At least, Kanah won't be disappointed yet.

347
00:26:05,880 --> 00:26:09,920
I don't know
if I can give him another chance.

348
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:14,520
If you can't, then don't.
It's not your job.

349
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:17,600
Your dad is the one
who has to do everything again

350
00:26:17,680 --> 00:26:19,960
if he wants to earn your trust again.

351
00:26:24,080 --> 00:26:25,200
Thank you.

352
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:31,240
Earlier in the afternoon,

353
00:26:32,160 --> 00:26:34,320
you heard what I said
to Mr. Rachen, didn't you?

354
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:40,560
I want to say what Rachen said too.

355
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:43,400
You're hurt and confused right now.

356
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:47,880
You should rest a bit.
Everything will get better.

357
00:26:59,880 --> 00:27:01,000
Mr. Trai,

358
00:27:02,800 --> 00:27:04,040
should we take a break?

359
00:27:12,440 --> 00:27:13,960
You want a break from us?

360
00:27:14,760 --> 00:27:17,360
Let's try taking a break
from this relationship

361
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:20,320
and go deal with our own problems.

362
00:27:20,920 --> 00:27:24,280
When everything's sorted,
we'll talk again.

363
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:27,720
So that means

364
00:27:29,080 --> 00:27:31,000
we're only going to love each other
when we're happy?

365
00:27:34,040 --> 00:27:35,880
I just want us to focus

366
00:27:36,800 --> 00:27:39,080
on what matters more.

367
00:27:47,440 --> 00:27:48,640
I understand.

368
00:27:50,080 --> 00:27:52,400
I'll go clear up my problems quickly.

369
00:27:54,120 --> 00:27:58,320
And I'll show you that having me
by your side when you're hurting

370
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:01,760
is better than being alone.

371
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:21,120
I'll wait until you reach
for my hand first…

372
00:28:24,560 --> 00:28:25,920
Then we'll hold hands.

373
00:28:49,720 --> 00:28:51,560
Because of my scandal,

374
00:28:51,640 --> 00:28:53,720
Be Rich has suffered damage.

375
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:57,720
I will take responsibility
by resigning as a board member,

376
00:28:57,800 --> 00:28:59,200
effective today.

377
00:29:01,280 --> 00:29:03,440
I, Trai Bowornmongkolphong,

378
00:29:04,040 --> 00:29:06,280
will have nothing
to do with Be Rich anymore.

379
00:29:08,200 --> 00:29:10,040
Finally, he's gone.

380
00:29:10,120 --> 00:29:12,360
You're resigning just to bury the news,

381
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:14,640
but you're still
a major shareholder, aren't you?

382
00:29:14,720 --> 00:29:16,400
No. I already sold my shares.

383
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:17,920
Huh?

384
00:29:18,560 --> 00:29:21,840
Mom, this works out for you, doesn't it?

385
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:23,080
And here

386
00:29:24,960 --> 00:29:26,880
is the major shareholder,

387
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:28,880
the current chairman of Be Rich.

388
00:29:31,840 --> 00:29:34,120
As for the alleged affair
between Darin and me,

389
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:37,320
I want to confirm again
that it is absolutely untrue.

390
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:41,800
And anyone who follows the page
that posted this story probably saw that

391
00:29:42,640 --> 00:29:45,160
this morning, the page
already posted an apology to me.

392
00:29:47,280 --> 00:29:49,840
And the page admin confirmed to me

393
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:52,120
that a certain businessperson

394
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:55,160
paid them to push this story
in order to discredit me.

395
00:29:56,720 --> 00:29:58,120
So it was a smear campaign?

396
00:29:58,200 --> 00:30:00,200
Do you know who it was?

397
00:30:00,280 --> 00:30:02,800
I'll just say… I know very well.

398
00:30:04,560 --> 00:30:05,960
- What's going on?
- Who was it?

399
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:06,960
Please tell us.

400
00:30:07,040 --> 00:30:09,040
- Just say it. Who was it?
- Who was it?

401
00:30:09,800 --> 00:30:11,000
Oh, Mrs. Mookmanee.

402
00:30:11,920 --> 00:30:12,840
Hello.

403
00:30:15,320 --> 00:30:17,360
She's my father's close friend.

404
00:30:17,440 --> 00:30:21,360
When I had problems,
she was always so concerned.

405
00:30:24,160 --> 00:30:26,480
You can ask Mrs. Mookmanee who framed me.

406
00:30:26,560 --> 00:30:28,920
Mrs. Mookmanee knows everything.

407
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:30,520
Huh? Knows everything?

408
00:30:30,600 --> 00:30:32,480
- Really?
- Really? Knows everything?

409
00:30:32,560 --> 00:30:34,440
So who was it, Mrs. Mookmanee,

410
00:30:34,520 --> 00:30:36,000
- that framed him?
- Please tell us.

411
00:30:36,080 --> 00:30:38,560
- Mrs. Mookmanee.
- You know who it was, don't you?

412
00:30:38,640 --> 00:30:40,680
Please tell us, Mrs. Mookmanee.

413
00:30:40,760 --> 00:30:41,880
Please tell us.

414
00:30:41,960 --> 00:30:43,000
Who was it?

415
00:30:43,080 --> 00:30:45,480
Mrs. Mookmanee, please tell us.

416
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:46,600
- Please tell us.
- Please tell us

417
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:47,560
- who it was.
- Yes.

418
00:30:47,640 --> 00:30:49,440
- Why did they do that?
- Please tell us.

419
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:51,760
Mrs. Mookmanee, please tell us who it was.

420
00:30:51,840 --> 00:30:53,080
Please.

421
00:30:56,560 --> 00:30:59,480
You didn't have to mess
with Mrs. Mookmanee like that.

422
00:30:59,560 --> 00:31:02,800
Why?
Worried about your future mother-in-law?

423
00:31:04,040 --> 00:31:06,360
I'm not planning to marry Mika anyway.

424
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:08,000
Right.

425
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:11,840
You're already
the biggest shareholder of Be Rich.

426
00:31:12,840 --> 00:31:14,720
Why marry for benefits? Right?

427
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:17,800
You're the one
who transferred the shares to me, Trai.

428
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:26,280
Then why didn't you step forward
when I talked about the chairman?

429
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:30,880
It was your scene.
I didn't want to steal it.

430
00:31:32,600 --> 00:31:34,000
Damn. That's cool.

431
00:31:35,840 --> 00:31:37,000
What are you two playing at?

432
00:31:37,520 --> 00:31:39,640
Oh, Mrs. Mookmanee. You managed
to shake the reporters off?

433
00:31:39,720 --> 00:31:40,760
How was it?

434
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:43,680
What did they grill you with?

435
00:31:43,760 --> 00:31:46,120
Any killer questions

436
00:31:46,200 --> 00:31:48,200
that I can use
to take legal action against you?

437
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:50,560
Trai, that's too much.

438
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:52,480
Don't you dare cross the line.

439
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:55,240
You think my mom framed you?

440
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:59,760
- Idiot! It was Rut.
- Mika, stop!

441
00:31:59,840 --> 00:32:04,360
Aha! Wow, you just let that slip yourself.

442
00:32:05,920 --> 00:32:09,840
Since you pulled strings to get him out,
how many dirty jobs have you had him do?

443
00:32:10,440 --> 00:32:12,480
You can thank your father for that.

444
00:32:13,080 --> 00:32:16,040
If Tritot hadn't tried so hard
to cover up his son's filth,

445
00:32:16,800 --> 00:32:18,200
Rut wouldn't have turned this rotten.

446
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:24,400
You really want to make an enemy of me?

447
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:28,440
No, of course not. I'd never dare.

448
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:31,520
Deep down, I want to be
on your side forever.

449
00:32:32,240 --> 00:32:36,640
But unfortunately, Mr. Park is waiting.

450
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:40,040
He's decided to invest in Be Rich.

451
00:32:40,120 --> 00:32:41,640
Excuse me.

452
00:33:00,640 --> 00:33:01,800
You're not leaving?

453
00:33:03,400 --> 00:33:06,240
When you leave, please turn off
the AC and the lights for me too.

454
00:33:07,520 --> 00:33:08,560
Thank you.

455
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:22,320
Yeah, I saw the news.

456
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:28,080
I just found out too.
Mr. Trai didn't tell me anything.

457
00:33:30,440 --> 00:33:32,040
I gotta go, Samlee.

458
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:36,160
I need to call the customer.
I don't know where they are.

459
00:33:43,280 --> 00:33:46,440
If Mr. Trai wants to give his Be Rich
shares to anyone, that's his business.

460
00:33:47,080 --> 00:33:49,520
Do you want him
to report to you all the time, Pakbung?

461
00:33:51,560 --> 00:33:53,240
Get a grip.

462
00:33:53,760 --> 00:33:55,920
Do your job, Pakbung.

463
00:33:58,240 --> 00:33:59,720
<i>You miss me, don't you?</i>

464
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:06,640
I'm talking trash about you, actually.

465
00:34:07,680 --> 00:34:09,719
<i>You want to see me, don't you?</i>

466
00:34:12,159 --> 00:34:13,480
Who wants to see you?

467
00:34:13,560 --> 00:34:16,639
<i>Shout my name three times,</i>
<i>and I'll come to you.</i>

468
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:22,520
Idiot. I'm working.

469
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:24,600
MR. TRAI

470
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:30,040
Hey, Mr. Trai,

471
00:34:30,120 --> 00:34:33,159
so now that you have no Be Rich shares,
you're totally free or what?

472
00:34:33,239 --> 00:34:36,360
You keep texting to mess with me.
I have to call a customer.

473
00:34:37,440 --> 00:34:39,120
Where's my bubble tea?

474
00:34:40,920 --> 00:34:41,840
Huh?

475
00:35:01,200 --> 00:35:02,960
You're using this trick again?

476
00:35:03,480 --> 00:35:05,560
Whose number did you use
to place the order this time?

477
00:35:06,400 --> 00:35:07,400
I'm not telling. You'll block it.

478
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:08,960
Not telling?

479
00:35:13,040 --> 00:35:14,000
This is my order, right?

480
00:35:16,880 --> 00:35:19,200
This cup is mine. The other one…

481
00:35:20,800 --> 00:35:21,800
is yours.

482
00:35:22,920 --> 00:35:23,760
Be careful.

483
00:35:28,640 --> 00:35:30,840
Hurry and drink it. It'll melt. Here.

484
00:35:33,040 --> 00:35:35,000
Hey.

485
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,800
So your solution

486
00:35:42,480 --> 00:35:44,680
is to just sell your shares to Mr. Rachen?

487
00:35:44,760 --> 00:35:46,840
Actually, I didn't sell them.

488
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:49,760
I gave them to him.

489
00:35:49,840 --> 00:35:51,000
Huh?

490
00:35:51,640 --> 00:35:52,640
You gave them?

491
00:35:55,800 --> 00:35:57,360
I made a promise with him

492
00:35:58,320 --> 00:36:00,520
that If I solve everything,

493
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:02,760
he'll transfer the shares back to me.

494
00:36:03,800 --> 00:36:05,240
What if Mr. Rachen doesn't give them back?

495
00:36:12,520 --> 00:36:14,360
Then I'll see his true colors.

496
00:36:15,960 --> 00:36:17,240
Hey, Mr. Trai,

497
00:36:18,560 --> 00:36:20,200
can I ask you for one thing?

498
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:29,360
If you ever want to give shares
to someone to solve a problem,

499
00:36:30,080 --> 00:36:31,480
next time, give them to me.

500
00:36:32,320 --> 00:36:33,880
Ugh, Pakbung.

501
00:36:34,880 --> 00:36:36,080
I'm serious.

502
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:39,720
If you give them to me,
I'll give you points.

503
00:36:40,560 --> 00:36:43,560
I'll stick a million stars
on your point-collecting card for you.

504
00:36:52,320 --> 00:36:55,120
You'd be the healthiest bubble tea ever.

505
00:36:57,320 --> 00:36:58,480
Hey,

506
00:36:58,560 --> 00:37:00,560
don't walk so fast. I can't--

507
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:07,600
Say one more word.

508
00:37:09,160 --> 00:37:10,200
You…

509
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:14,760
Drink it all. It's over 100 baht a cup.

510
00:37:21,600 --> 00:37:23,680
You told me not to use violence,

511
00:37:23,760 --> 00:37:25,320
but you're even worse than me.

512
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:32,200
Take this money and get your face fixed.

513
00:37:32,880 --> 00:37:34,760
If it doesn't heal,
don't ever show your face here again.

514
00:37:36,440 --> 00:37:39,680
I'm sorry, Mrs. Mookmanee.

515
00:37:48,040 --> 00:37:50,720
I won't let everything
I've done go to waste.

516
00:37:51,680 --> 00:37:52,680
You have to handle it for me.

517
00:37:55,400 --> 00:37:57,120
The siblings have united.

518
00:37:57,200 --> 00:37:59,480
Going after just one of them
would probably be difficult.

519
00:37:59,560 --> 00:38:01,080
So you can't do it?

520
00:38:01,880 --> 00:38:04,000
No, ma'am. I'm just saying

521
00:38:04,680 --> 00:38:08,400
if we make them turn on each other
and deal with each other, it'd be easier.

522
00:38:17,880 --> 00:38:18,960
Alright.

523
00:38:24,360 --> 00:38:27,240
From now on, Mrs. Mookmanee probably
won't be able to mess with Be Rich.

524
00:38:27,960 --> 00:38:29,240
But she won't stop too easily.

525
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:32,240
That's what I think too.

526
00:38:34,720 --> 00:38:35,680
What are you gonna do next?

527
00:38:36,400 --> 00:38:38,680
I have to find evidence to take
legal action against Mrs. Mookmanee.

528
00:38:39,640 --> 00:38:43,240
Someone with dirty hands like that
has to leave some kind of trace.

529
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:48,640
What?

530
00:38:55,680 --> 00:38:59,680
Didn't you say you'd only hold my hand
when I reached out mine to you first?

531
00:39:00,280 --> 00:39:02,880
No. I don't mean your hand.

532
00:39:02,960 --> 00:39:03,960
I mean my pay.

533
00:39:05,440 --> 00:39:07,400
I did delivery jobs
with you all day today.

534
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:09,040
You have to pay me wages too.

535
00:39:09,120 --> 00:39:10,320
Wait.

536
00:39:11,440 --> 00:39:14,760
I didn't ask you to come with me.

537
00:39:14,840 --> 00:39:16,440
But you didn't kick me out, did you?

538
00:39:17,920 --> 00:39:18,880
Let me see.

539
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:20,880
- How much did you get?
- What?

540
00:39:20,960 --> 00:39:23,480
- Hey. Let go.
- Wow.

541
00:39:23,560 --> 00:39:24,920
Can you give me one-third?

542
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:27,120
- Hey.
- I'm not giving you anything.

543
00:39:27,200 --> 00:39:29,720
Are you some kind of extortion gang?
I'm not giving you anything.

544
00:39:30,640 --> 00:39:33,840
Come on. I don't have shares anymore.
I'm poorer than you now.

545
00:39:37,160 --> 00:39:38,560
Can't I leech off you a little?

546
00:39:40,200 --> 00:39:42,720
Mr. Trai, are you mocking me?

547
00:39:48,480 --> 00:39:50,320
Hey? What?

548
00:39:50,400 --> 00:39:51,640
Then just give me money for the ride home.

549
00:39:52,320 --> 00:39:53,640
I said no.

550
00:39:53,720 --> 00:39:55,560
Let go now. Let go.

551
00:39:55,640 --> 00:39:56,680
I said let go.

552
00:39:56,760 --> 00:39:58,760
Then, I'll take one kiss.

553
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:02,960
Hey! Mr. Trai!

554
00:40:03,600 --> 00:40:05,880
You're crazy.
How can you kiss my cheek right here?

555
00:40:05,960 --> 00:40:08,240
- Are you gonna let go?
- Ouch.

556
00:40:08,320 --> 00:40:11,560
You elbowed me? I'm still not
feeling tired, so I'll take another one.

557
00:40:11,640 --> 00:40:13,080
Hey. Hey!

558
00:40:15,040 --> 00:40:16,880
Let go of me now.

559
00:40:16,960 --> 00:40:20,440
You pervert. You madman.
How can you kiss me here?

560
00:40:25,080 --> 00:40:26,520
If you dream about me, I charge money.

561
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:31,280
If you show up in my dreams,

562
00:40:31,360 --> 00:40:33,160
I'll cut your points down to zero.

563
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:37,160
Let's go, baby.

564
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:58,680
<i>I have to find evidence to take</i>
<i>legal action against Mrs. Mookmanee.</i>

565
00:40:59,560 --> 00:41:03,560
<i>Someone with dirty hands like that</i>
<i>has to leave some kind of trace.</i>

566
00:41:13,200 --> 00:41:15,400
Pakbung, you wanted
to talk to me about something?

567
00:41:17,960 --> 00:41:19,440
I'll get straight to it.

568
00:41:22,400 --> 00:41:23,640
You know, right?

569
00:41:23,720 --> 00:41:25,840
That Mrs. Mookmanee isn't a good person.

570
00:41:27,440 --> 00:41:28,360
Why are you asking?

571
00:41:29,080 --> 00:41:31,200
Because if we want to live together again,

572
00:41:31,920 --> 00:41:33,920
I want to trust you.

573
00:41:36,800 --> 00:41:40,280
Mrs. Mookmanee has been so cruel to me.

574
00:41:40,360 --> 00:41:43,400
If she gets arrested, I'd be so happy.

575
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:44,800
So…

576
00:41:46,560 --> 00:41:49,480
can you find evidence that Mrs. Mookmanee

577
00:41:49,560 --> 00:41:51,280
has done something illegal?

578
00:41:51,360 --> 00:41:53,160
Anything… stock fraud, any fraud at all.

579
00:41:53,240 --> 00:41:54,960
Can you help find it for me?

580
00:41:55,960 --> 00:41:56,880
Pakbung.

581
00:41:56,960 --> 00:41:59,600
I can't do that. I got thrown out.

582
00:41:59,680 --> 00:42:01,080
I can't go back.

583
00:42:03,120 --> 00:42:04,400
You're such a good actor.

584
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:07,280
Something this simple
is not beyond your ability.

585
00:42:08,400 --> 00:42:10,720
But it's really hard, Pakbung. I…

586
00:42:10,800 --> 00:42:13,240
I was just asking. I already knew

587
00:42:13,320 --> 00:42:16,240
that you never really planned
to do anything for me.

588
00:42:42,080 --> 00:42:43,120
Mrs. Mook,

589
00:42:43,640 --> 00:42:46,280
I… I've realized my mistakes.

590
00:42:46,960 --> 00:42:51,360
Please let me come back
and serve you here again.

591
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:54,280
What did you do wrong?
Why are you apologizing?

592
00:42:55,000 --> 00:42:57,480
Well… I…

593
00:42:57,560 --> 00:43:01,360
You just went out to be with your family.
That's not a mistake.

594
00:43:01,440 --> 00:43:04,640
I even saw that you looked happy.
Why come back?

595
00:43:07,400 --> 00:43:10,320
Well… I…

596
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:13,120
I went back to gambling.

597
00:43:13,200 --> 00:43:17,400
I'm addicted to gambling.
And I'm in debt too.

598
00:43:17,480 --> 00:43:19,880
I really have nowhere to go, Mrs. Mook.

599
00:43:20,480 --> 00:43:22,480
Can you give me one more chance?

600
00:43:22,560 --> 00:43:25,280
I swear, whatever you want me to do,

601
00:43:25,360 --> 00:43:26,800
I'll do.

602
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:37,760
I want to trust you.

603
00:43:40,640 --> 00:43:41,920
But I'd rather not.

604
00:43:43,680 --> 00:43:44,880
Get out.

605
00:43:45,600 --> 00:43:47,280
- Mrs. Mook…
- Get out.

606
00:43:51,240 --> 00:43:52,520
Yes.

607
00:44:07,080 --> 00:44:10,400
Bunny Bunny.
Electrolytes to boost your energy.

608
00:44:10,480 --> 00:44:13,600
Easy to drink. Try a sample first!

609
00:44:15,640 --> 00:44:18,000
Here, please try it.

610
00:44:18,080 --> 00:44:19,600
It boosts your energy.

611
00:44:21,040 --> 00:44:22,520
Hey.

612
00:44:22,600 --> 00:44:25,040
Did Uncle Yongyut really agree
to go back and find evidence for you?

613
00:44:27,400 --> 00:44:29,320
I woke up, and he was gone.

614
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:31,560
If he didn't go to help,
then he probably ran away.

615
00:44:31,640 --> 00:44:36,280
Oh. And are you okay
with your dad actually going?

616
00:44:37,160 --> 00:44:38,360
Of course.

617
00:44:38,440 --> 00:44:40,280
It's better than
being paranoid all the time.

618
00:44:40,360 --> 00:44:43,280
If he doesn't come back, then it's clear.

619
00:44:43,360 --> 00:44:45,080
No need to force it or endure it anymore.

620
00:44:46,160 --> 00:44:49,640
If Uncle Yongyut really does it for you,
that's good.

621
00:45:36,480 --> 00:45:39,880
Mrs. Mook… What's the password?

622
00:46:08,880 --> 00:46:09,920
Huh?

623
00:46:23,640 --> 00:46:25,120
I knew you'd betray me.

624
00:46:26,400 --> 00:46:27,920
Trai sent you, didn't he?

625
00:46:28,720 --> 00:46:32,120
Uh, no, no, no. No, Mrs. Mook.

626
00:46:33,800 --> 00:46:35,320
No one sent me at all.

627
00:46:35,400 --> 00:46:39,800
I just want money to pay my debt,
and I thought

628
00:46:39,880 --> 00:46:42,040
you would keep money in here.

629
00:46:42,120 --> 00:46:45,360
Mrs. Mook, I really need money.

630
00:46:45,440 --> 00:46:46,920
Please have mercy on me.

631
00:46:49,600 --> 00:46:51,680
How am I supposed to have mercy
on someone like you?

632
00:46:54,000 --> 00:46:54,840
Mrs. Mook…

633
00:46:54,920 --> 00:46:56,960
If you don't trust him,

634
00:46:58,360 --> 00:47:00,560
why don't you let him prove himself

635
00:47:01,680 --> 00:47:03,480
and see if he only wants money or not?

636
00:47:16,160 --> 00:47:19,360
Please, Mrs. Mook. Please believe me.

637
00:47:31,880 --> 00:47:32,720
DAD

638
00:47:34,360 --> 00:47:35,760
<i>I've got it.</i>

639
00:47:38,520 --> 00:47:40,120
<i>Come meet me here tonight</i>

640
00:47:40,640 --> 00:47:42,520
Over here, please.

641
00:47:44,800 --> 00:47:46,120
Who messaged you?

642
00:47:48,360 --> 00:47:50,480
Some spam. It's nothing.

643
00:47:54,760 --> 00:47:55,800
Customers.

644
00:47:58,520 --> 00:47:59,880
- You can try this.
- Please take it.

645
00:47:59,960 --> 00:48:02,480
You'll feel so refreshed
after drinking it.

646
00:48:04,680 --> 00:48:06,080
It's good.

647
00:48:30,800 --> 00:48:32,240
This is B11.

648
00:48:34,880 --> 00:48:35,960
Where's Dad?

649
00:48:41,800 --> 00:48:43,040
Dad?

650
00:48:44,720 --> 00:48:47,840
Dad, is that you?

651
00:48:49,160 --> 00:48:50,120
Dad.

652
00:48:52,120 --> 00:48:53,360
Dad?

653
00:49:15,320 --> 00:49:16,720
Mr. Trai.

654
00:49:17,840 --> 00:49:19,040
That's not your dad.

655
00:49:40,960 --> 00:49:42,120
Then where's my dad?

656
00:49:44,080 --> 00:49:45,160
What happened?

657
00:49:46,240 --> 00:49:47,320
Why did the power go out?

658
00:49:48,360 --> 00:49:49,320
Or did they realize?

659
00:49:50,960 --> 00:49:52,160
Are you trying to play tricks on me?

660
00:49:52,240 --> 00:49:53,920
You signaled your daughter, didn't you?

661
00:49:54,000 --> 00:49:55,760
No, Mrs. Mook.

662
00:49:55,840 --> 00:49:59,480
I sent Pakbung the messages
exactly like you ordered.

663
00:49:59,560 --> 00:50:02,440
If you don't believe me,
you can check it yourself.

664
00:50:02,960 --> 00:50:05,280
Then call her. You want money, don't you?

665
00:50:06,320 --> 00:50:08,080
Call your daughter over here,
and I'll transfer it.

666
00:50:19,200 --> 00:50:20,120
Is it that hard?

667
00:50:25,560 --> 00:50:26,600
Give it to me.

668
00:50:40,440 --> 00:50:41,720
Pakbung.

669
00:50:43,520 --> 00:50:44,960
Where are you?

670
00:50:46,040 --> 00:50:48,200
What's going on? Why did the power go out?

671
00:50:48,800 --> 00:50:50,160
I don't know.

672
00:50:50,960 --> 00:50:52,520
Where are you?

673
00:50:54,120 --> 00:50:55,760
I'm in the parking lot.

674
00:50:57,400 --> 00:50:59,240
I saw your motorcycle,

675
00:51:00,720 --> 00:51:02,360
but I don't know where you are.

676
00:51:14,640 --> 00:51:15,760
Pakbung…

677
00:51:17,520 --> 00:51:19,840
<i>Pakbung, can you walk over to me?</i>

678
00:51:22,240 --> 00:51:27,040
I'm… I'm hiding by the last pillar.

679
00:51:29,760 --> 00:51:32,040
You really want me to go there?

680
00:51:49,880 --> 00:51:51,200
Yes.

681
00:51:53,520 --> 00:51:55,320
Walk over to me here.

682
00:52:07,520 --> 00:52:10,800
What kind of father are you? Luring
your own daughter here to get her killed?

683
00:52:12,840 --> 00:52:14,320
You're fucking disgusting!

684
00:52:56,800 --> 00:52:58,040
Hello.

685
00:53:57,280 --> 00:53:59,120
How did you make it in time to help me?

686
00:54:01,800 --> 00:54:03,280
Samlee and Niuniu told me.

687
00:54:04,440 --> 00:54:05,640
Do you want to scold me?

688
00:54:08,200 --> 00:54:10,600
Scold you? Why would I?

689
00:54:11,480 --> 00:54:13,080
I walked right into trouble.

690
00:54:14,480 --> 00:54:16,760
I rushed there alone.

691
00:54:17,520 --> 00:54:19,480
Can you scold me?

692
00:54:20,520 --> 00:54:21,800
Just scold me hard.

693
00:54:21,880 --> 00:54:23,040
Pakbung…

694
00:54:25,400 --> 00:54:27,120
When I got that message,

695
00:54:28,320 --> 00:54:30,440
I knew something felt off. I wondered

696
00:54:31,880 --> 00:54:34,000
if he was lying to me again.

697
00:54:35,440 --> 00:54:37,240
But I still went.

698
00:54:39,760 --> 00:54:43,680
I wanted to know how it would end,

699
00:54:44,640 --> 00:54:46,800
how bad it could get…

700
00:54:48,080 --> 00:54:49,640
But I never thought

701
00:54:50,840 --> 00:54:52,520
it would go this far.

702
00:54:54,080 --> 00:54:55,280
That he would…

703
00:54:56,360 --> 00:54:57,440
trick me…

704
00:54:59,160 --> 00:55:00,080
into getting killed.

705
00:55:46,480 --> 00:55:48,960
Mrs. Mook.

706
00:55:49,040 --> 00:55:51,320
I really didn't know

707
00:55:51,400 --> 00:55:53,000
that Mr. Trai would come.

708
00:55:53,080 --> 00:55:54,640
- I swear.
- Give me the gun.

709
00:55:55,600 --> 00:55:56,400
Mrs. Mook.

710
00:55:58,720 --> 00:56:02,160
Mrs. Mook, please. I…

711
00:56:03,200 --> 00:56:05,680
I'm not your stupid daughter

712
00:56:06,200 --> 00:56:08,560
who believes your every word
and lets you fool her again and again.

713
00:56:10,520 --> 00:56:14,600
If you dare betray me like this,
there's only one ending for you.

714
00:56:14,680 --> 00:56:17,800
Please, Mrs. Mook. No. I'm begging you.

715
00:56:17,880 --> 00:56:19,880
Mrs. Mook. Mrs. Mook.

716
00:56:20,920 --> 00:56:22,240
No, please. Mrs. Mook.

717
00:56:22,320 --> 00:56:23,160
Mrs. Mook.

718
00:56:25,440 --> 00:56:26,920
The police are here.

719
00:56:37,360 --> 00:56:39,840
Yes. I reported that Mr. Yongyut

720
00:56:39,920 --> 00:56:41,920
is involved in running
an illegal gambling den.

721
00:56:44,040 --> 00:56:46,680
The police have taken Mr. Yongyut.

722
00:56:47,880 --> 00:56:49,680
They're taking him in for questioning.

723
00:56:51,520 --> 00:56:54,000
Please take care of him.
Don't let anything happen to him.

724
00:56:55,000 --> 00:56:57,040
I don't want Pakbung
to get hurt more than she already is.

725
00:56:58,240 --> 00:56:59,160
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

726
00:57:00,800 --> 00:57:01,920
Thanks.

727
00:57:37,480 --> 00:57:38,560
Dad…

728
00:58:19,760 --> 00:58:23,040
If you can bring us proof
of Mrs. Mookmanee's crimes,

729
00:58:23,120 --> 00:58:24,760
we'll reward you

730
00:58:24,840 --> 00:58:26,480
as much as you want.

731
00:58:27,360 --> 00:58:29,120
Can your secretary be trusted?

732
00:58:29,200 --> 00:58:31,600
No one would ever betray my money.

733
00:58:31,680 --> 00:58:33,960
And what if Trai
didn't use money to lure him?

734
00:58:34,040 --> 00:58:35,880
I'll write a suicide note for you.

735
00:58:37,800 --> 00:58:38,960
No. Don't!

736
00:58:45,520 --> 00:58:47,320
This isn't enough to take me down.

737
00:58:48,320 --> 00:58:49,400
Who said this is all?

738
00:58:49,480 --> 00:58:50,320
Excuse me.

739
00:58:50,400 --> 00:58:51,680
Mom.

740
00:58:51,760 --> 00:58:54,200
<i>I'll use that arrogant little rich girl</i>

741
00:58:54,280 --> 00:58:57,120
to get back at Trai
and deal with Pakbung for you.

742
00:58:58,240 --> 00:58:59,720
What is Rut going to do to Pakbung?

743
00:58:59,800 --> 00:59:03,520
Look. Your daughter is about to become
a murderer in front of the whole world.

744
00:59:03,600 --> 00:59:05,960
Even if you kneel and beg me now,
it's too late. Do you hear me?

745
00:59:08,280 --> 00:59:09,680
Hey! Hey!

746
00:59:57,120 --> 00:59:59,680
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
